data.name: Truffle Tagliatelle with Wild Mushrooms
data.quickTastyDescription: A luxurious dish combining silky tagliatelle with earthy wild mushrooms, drizzled with aromatic truffle oil for a gourmet experience.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook the tagliatelle in boiling salted water according to package instructions until al dente, usually about 8-10 minutes.
While the pasta is cooking, clean and slice the wild mushrooms and chop the garlic.
In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the garlic and saut√© for 1 minute until fragrant.
Add the mushrooms to the skillet and cook for about 5-7 minutes until they're tender and golden. Season with salt and black pepper.
Once the pasta is cooked, reserve a cup of pasta water and drain the rest.
Add the drained tagliatelle to the skillet with the mushrooms. Toss everything together, adding a splash of the reserved pasta water to create a light sauce.
Drizzle the truffle oil over the pasta and toss gently to combine. Adjust seasoning if needed.
Serve in bowls, garnished with freshly grated Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley.
data.modifiersForBase: with wild mushrooms and truffle oil
